    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avius</ex></expan> Campestrinus <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>vet</abbr><ex>eranus</ex></expan> et <expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex>ia</ex></expan> Exora<lb break="no" n="3"/>ta <expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex>io</ex></expan> Exorato <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>lib</abbr><ex>rario</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulari</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fil</abbr><ex>io</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>ob</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> XX <lb n="5"/>et Secundinio Can<lb break="no" n="6"/>didiano b<expan><ex>ene</ex><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iciario</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulari</ex></expan> ge<lb break="no" n="7"/>nero vivi fecerunt
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes weibliche und männliche Büste; auf der linken Nebenseite Krater, aus dem eine spiralförmige Ranke wächst. Nach Kremer wohl Schaftblock eines altar- oder pfeilerförmigen Grabbaus. (B): Zabehlicky-Scheffenegger: Z. 5: Secundino; Zabehlicky-Scheffenegger; Eckhart; Kremer: Z. 5/6: Can/d[i]diano.</p>
            </div>
